  "prompt": "Which USA universities have late deadline for master in AI , ML or vision? (For Fall)",
  "response": "As of my most recent update, deadlines for Fall admissions to Master's programs in AI, ML, or Computer Vision can vary widely among U.S. universities. Typically, deadlines for Fall admission range from December to February, with many top programs having deadlines in December or January. However, some universities may have later deadlines or offer rolling admissions, which can provide more flexibility.\n\nHere are a few universities and points to consider if you're looking for programs with late deadlines or rolling admissions for Fall intake:\n\n1. **Northeastern University (Align MS in Computer Science)**  \n   - Offers a late deadline (often in April or May) for Fall admission.  \n   - Focus on AI/ML through the College of Computer and Information Science.  \n\n2. **University of Southern California (USC)**  \n   - Some MS programs in Computer Science (with AI/ML specializations) may have deadlines as late as February or March.  \n\n3. **University of Illinois Chicago (UIC)**  \n   - Offers rolling admissions for its MS in Computer Science program, with deadline extensions often available.  \n\n4. **Arizona State University (ASU)**  \n   - Deadlines for MS in Computer Science (with AI/ML focus) can extend into March or April.  \n\n5. **University of San Francisco (MS in Data Science)**  \n   - Offers a late deadline (often March or April) for Fall admission.  \n\n6. **University of California, Riverside (UCR)**  \n   - MS in Computer Science has deadlines as late as March or April.  \n\n7. **Syracuse University**  \n   - Offers rolling admissions for its MS in Computer Science program, with deadlines extending into the spring.  \n\n8. **University of Texas at Dallas (UT Dallas)**  \n   - MS in Computer Science (AI/ML focus) has deadlines as late as March or April.  \n\n9. **Drexel University**  \n   - Offers rolling admissions for its MS in Computer Science program, with deadlines extending into the spring.  \n\n10. **University of Central Florida (UCF)**  \n    - MS in Computer Science (AI/ML focus) has deadlines as late as March or April.  \n\n### Notes:  \n- **Rolling Admissions:** Some universities with rolling admissions may accept applications well into the spring or until the program is full.  \n- **Deadline Extensions:** Some universities may offer extensions to their deadlines, so it\u2019s worth reaching out to the admissions office if you\u2019re close to a deadline.  \n- **Program-Specific Deadlines:** Always check the specific program\u2019s website for the most accurate and up-to-date deadline information.  \n\nFor the most accurate and updated deadlines, visit the official websites of the universities and their respective graduate admissions offices.",
